[Please note that reports in these updates have been edited to replace
"flu-like", "Norwalk-like", "bug", et alia, with the International
Committee on the Taxonomy of Viruses (ICTV) approved designation
"Norovirus" for the calicivirus presumed or confirmed to be responsible for
sudden onset viral gastroenteritis. - Mod.CP]
